io.spine.server.model

Interface HandlerMethod<M extends io.spine.type.MessageClass,C extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - the type of the message class
    C - the type of the message context or Empty if a context parameter is never used
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CommandingMethod<M,C>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractHandlerMethod, CommandAcceptingMethod, CommandHandlerMethod, CommandSubstituteMethod, EventApplier, EventReactorMethod, EventSubscriberMethod, RejectionReactorMethod, RejectionSubscriberMethod

    public interface HandlerMethod<M extends io.spine.type.MessageClass,C extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
    Describes a method that accepts a message and optionally its context.

    Two message handlers are equivalent when they refer to the same method on the same object (not class).
